					<br /><b>Joined:</b> Wed Mar 22, 2006 8:00 am<br /><b>Posts:</b> 354
				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If your game is a vertical scroller, consider updating nametables 1 line at a time, as each line scrolls into view, rather than updating the whole nametable at once.  This way, you don't have to turn off the screen during updates since there's plenty of VBlank time to update a single row of tiles per frame.
<br />
<br />Display should only be turned on/off during VBlank.  Also, you should always use NMI to detect VBlank instead of $2002 polling (except on power-up).</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />"Last version was better," says Floyd. "More bugs. Bugs make game fun."</div>
